Combined by the calculated J value and equation (2) (where ΦD, the fluorescence quantum yield of SiNDs is 16%), the distance between the donor and acceptor (R0 value) is determined to be 3.5 nm, which meet the distance of FRET theory from between 1 nm and 10 nm. Besides, the average fluorescent lifetime of GCPF becomes shorter after the addition of PA (
                        Fig. 8
